Package: disbayes
Title: Bayesian evidence synthesis for chronic disease epidemiology
Version: 0.1
Author: Chris Jackson <chris.jackson@mrc-bsu.cam.ac.uk>
Maintainer: Chris Jackson <chris.jackson@mrc-bsu.cam.ac.uk>
Description: Estimation of incidence and case fatality for a chronic disease, given partial information, using a multi-state model. Given data on age-specific mortality and either incidence or prevalence, Bayesian inference is used to estimate the posterior distributions of incidence, case fatality, and functions of these such as prevalence. 
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
